John R. Ciulla  President, President of Webster Bank and Director of Webster Bank, Webster Financial CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 2 different industries.See Board Relationships51$1,317,366As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. John R. Ciulla has been the President of Webster Financial Corp.  and Webster Bank, N.A. since October 28, 2015. Mr. Ciulla has been the President of Fairfield and Westchester Counties Region of Webster Bank N.A. since September 17, 2007. He serves as Executive Vice President of Commercial Banking at Webster Financial Corp. Mr. Ciulla served as an Executive Vice President of Commercial Banking at Webster Financial Corporation and Webster Bank, National Association ... since January 1, 2014. He served as Chief Credit Risk Officer and Executive Vice President of Webster Bank National Association, a subsidiary of Webster Financial Corp. from January 2008 to January 1, 2014 and as its Chairman of Regional President Council since September 2010. Mr. Ciulla served as the Head of Middle Market banking group at Webster Bank, National Association from September 2010 to January 1, 2014. He served as Executive Vice President of Middle Market - Webster Bank N A of Webster Financial Corp. He joined Webster Bank NA and serves as its Senior Vice President of Commercial Banking Unit. Mr. Ciulla assumes the added responsibilities of coordinating Webster's business and community affairs activities in this region. He served as Managing Director of Media & Communications of FirstLight Financial Corporation.  He spent three years in commercial banking with Webster. His career includes having been Managing Director of The Bank of New York, practicing law in New York City with McDermott Will & Emery and with Hughes Hubbard & Reed and banking experience with Bankers Trust Company in New York, People's Bank in Bridgeport and Connecticut National Bank in Hartford and New Haven. He has been a Director of Webster Bank, N.A. since October 28, 2015. Mr. Ciulla holds B.A. in political science and history from Williams College and has a J.D. from Fordham University and an M.B.A. from Columbia University.Read Full Background




